---
pagination:
  data: products
  size: 1
  alias: product
  resolve: values
permalink: "/products/{{ product.slug }}/"
layout: layouts/base.njk
eleventyComputed:
  title: "{{ product.name }}"
  description: "What {{ product.name }} contains now. Every fact is shown with its source, confidence and evidence level; anything not yet verified is withheld rather than asserted."
---
{% from "components/macros.njk" import sourcedValue, sourceNote, caveatBox %}

{#
  One server-rendered page per product. The src/_data/products/* cascade is an
  OBJECT keyed by filename, so the front-matter pagination uses resolve: values:
  default pagination over an object iterates its KEYS (strings), which would break
  every template (03a-RESEARCH.md Pattern 1 / Pitfall 2). Hyphenated keys
  (products.spike-01) are also invalid Nunjucks dot access; paginating over values
  sidesteps that. A1 is smoke-verified by asserting the product NAME (not a
  filename) renders on a built page.
#}

<h1>{{ product.name }}</h1>

<p class="lede">The current declared record for {{ product.name }}. Each value is shown through the trust component: a fact appears only once it has met the verification standard its claim type demands, and is otherwise marked "not yet verified; withheld".</p>

{#
  Sections follow the LOCKED D-05 order: Ingredients, Nutrition, Allergens,
  Manufacturer, Sources, Recipe history. This plan (03a-03) authors Ingredients,
  Manufacturer, Sources and Recipe history. Plan 04 inserts the Nutrition and
  Allergens h2 sections between Ingredients and Manufacturer, in that order; the
  placeholder comment below marks where they slot in so the outline stays gap-free.
#}

<section id="ingredients" aria-labelledby="ingredients-heading">
  <h2 id="ingredients-heading">Ingredients</h2>
  <p>The current declared ingredients list. This is the sourced recipe of record; it is not broken out into individual ingredient entries here.</p>
  {%- if product.ingredientsText %}
  {{ sourcedValue(product.ingredientsText, sources.sources, "Declared ingredients", "", "product") }}
  {%- else %}
  <p class="example">No declared ingredients list has been sourced for this product yet.</p>
  {%- endif %}
</section>

{# PLAN 04 INSERTS HERE, in D-05 order:
   <section id="nutrition"> ... </section>  (the nutrition table, D-06)
   <section id="allergens"> ... </section>  (the allergen fail-safe list, D-12)
   Do not reorder; Manufacturer, Sources and Recipe history must stay after them. #}

<section id="manufacturer" aria-labelledby="manufacturer-heading">
  <h2 id="manufacturer-heading">Manufacturer</h2>
  {%- if product.manufacturer %}
  {{ sourcedValue(product.manufacturer, sources.sources, "Made by", "", "product") }}
  {%- else %}
  <p class="example">No manufacturer has been sourced for this product yet.</p>
  {%- endif %}
</section>

{#
  Sources roll-up (PROD-04, D-07): the page-level list of the distinct source
  records cited by this page's facts. The per-fact "Source and date" disclosure
  still lives on each fact above; this is the consolidated view. Collect the ids
  cited by the facts this plan renders (manufacturer, ingredientsText); plan 04's
  Nutrition and Allergens sections extend the collection below when they land.
  Dedup is stateless: an id renders only at its FIRST occurrence in the list
  (citedIds.indexOf(id) == loop.index0), because Nunjucks {% set %} inside a for
  loop does not persist across iterations. Source names and urls are ingested and
  external, so they are never piped through | safe; external links carry
  rel="noopener" (threat T-03a-03-02).
#}
{%- set citedIds = [] %}
{%- if product.manufacturer and product.manufacturer.sources %}{% set citedIds = citedIds.concat(product.manufacturer.sources) %}{% endif %}
{%- if product.ingredientsText and product.ingredientsText.sources %}{% set citedIds = citedIds.concat(product.ingredientsText.sources) %}{% endif %}
<section id="sources" aria-labelledby="sources-heading">
  <h2 id="sources-heading">Sources</h2>
  {%- if citedIds.length %}
  <p>The sources cited by the facts on this page. Each fact above also shows its own source and date behind its "Source and date" disclosure.</p>
  <ul class="source-roll">
    {%- for id in citedIds %}
    {%- if citedIds.indexOf(id) == loop.index0 %}
    {%- set s = sources.sources | findBy("id", id) %}
    <li>
      {%- if s %}
      {% if s.url %}<a href="{{ s.url }}" rel="noopener">{{ s.name }}</a>{% else %}{{ s.name }}{% endif %}{% if s.jurisdiction %} ({{ s.jurisdiction }}){% endif %}.
      {%- else %}
      Unresolved source reference: {{ id }}.
      {%- endif %}
    </li>
    {%- endif %}
    {%- endfor %}
  </ul>
  {%- else %}
  <p class="example">No sources have been cited on this page yet.</p>
  {%- endif %}
</section>

{#
  Recipe history (PROD-02/03, SC3). Events are joined by the timelineByProduct
  reverse index (global from 03a-01). Each event's documentedChange and
  statedReason are sourced facts, rendered through the trust component with
  entityType "timeline" (historical facts, never stale). labelledInference is NOT
  a fact (it has no sources or claimType) and is rendered as a labelled
  illustration paragraph ONLY, never through the trust component (threat
  T-03a-03-03). Where a product has no sourced change events, the honest empty
  state renders (SC3, "absent, not a broken stub"), never a withheld or error
  card. The conditional "full timeline" link renders only where a Phase 8 timeline
  page exists (none do yet, so it is omitted).
#}
<section id="recipe-history" aria-labelledby="recipe-history-heading">
  <h2 id="recipe-history-heading">Recipe history</h2>
  {%- set events = timelineByProduct[product.id] %}
  {%- if events and events.length %}
  <p>Sourced, dated changes to this product's formulation. Each change shows its source, date and confidence; a value that its sources genuinely disagree on is shown as contested, with both positions.</p>
  {%- for e in events %}
  <article class="change-event">
    <h3>
      {%- if e.date.from or e.date.to %}
      Changed {{ e.date.from }} to {{ e.date.to }}{% if e.date.basis %} ({{ e.date.basis }}){% endif %}
      {%- else %}
      Changed {{ e.date | readableDate }}
      {%- endif %}
    </h3>
    {%- for c in e.changes %}
    {%- if c.documentedChange %}{{ sourcedValue(c.documentedChange, sources.sources, "Documented change", "", "timeline") }}{% endif %}
    {%- if c.statedReason %}{{ sourcedValue(c.statedReason, sources.sources, "Stated reason", "", "timeline") }}{% endif %}
    {%- if c.labelledInference %}
    <p class="example"><strong>Labelled inference:</strong> {{ c.labelledInference.text }}</p>
    {%- endif %}
    {%- endfor %}
  </article>
  {%- endfor %}
  {%- else %}
  <div class="example">
    <h3>No recipe changes recorded yet</h3>
    <p>We have not yet sourced and verified any formulation changes for this product. When we do, they will appear here, each with its source and date.</p>
  </div>
  {%- endif %}
</section>
</content>
